args.new_str:
def get_filtered_matrix(group_option, prompt_variation, model_id, excluded_ids):  # not the full matrix
    group_list = group_mappings[group_option]
    full_group_list = ['a person'] + group_list
    n = len(full_group_list)
    matrix_raw = np.zeros((n, n))
    for i, persona in enumerate(full_group_list):
        for j, experiencer in enumerate(full_group_list):
            intensity_list, _ = get_intensity_list(group_option, prompt_variation, model_id, persona, experiencer)
            filtered = [x for idx, x in enumerate(intensity_list) if idx not in excluded_ids]
            if filtered:
                matrix_raw[i, j] = np.mean(filtered)
            else:
                matrix_raw[i, j] = np.nan
    # Standardize (z-score) using only non-nan values
    valid = ~np.isnan(matrix_raw)
    mu = np.nanmean(matrix_raw)
    sigma = np.nanstd(matrix_raw)
    matrix = (matrix_raw - mu) / sigma
    return matrix
